{"title_page": "Tony Award for Best Direction of a Play", "text_new": "{{Infobox award\n| name        = [[Tony Award]] for <br>Best Direction of a Play\n| description = Best Direction of a Play\n| presenter   = [[American Theatre Wing]] [[The Broadway League]]\n| location    = [[New York City]]\n| holder      = [[Sam Mendes]] for ''[[The Ferryman (play)|The Ferryman]]'' {{small|(2019)}}\n| website     = [http://www.tonyawards.com/en_US/index.html TonyAwards.com]\n}}\nThe '''[[Tony Award]] for Best Direction of a Play''' has been given since 1960.  Before 1960 there was only one award for both play direction and musical direction, then in 1960 the award was split into two categories: ''Dramatic'' and ''Musical''.  In 1976 the Dramatic category was renamed to Play.  For pre-1960 direction awards please reference [[Tony Award for Best Director]].\n\n==Winners and nominees==\n{{legend|#B0C4DE|indicates the winner}}\n\n===1960s===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:98%;\"\n|- style=\"background:#bebebe;\"\n! style=\"width:11%;\"| Year\n! style=\"width:35%;\"| Director\n! style=\"width:54%;\"| Production\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\" align=\"center\"| '''1960'''<br>{{small|[[14th Tony Awards]]}}\n|- style=\"background:#B0C4DE\"\n| [[Arthur Penn]]\n| ''[[The Miracle Worker (play)|The Miracle Worker]]''\n|-\n| [[Joseph Anthony]]\n| ''[[The Best Man (play)|The Best Man]]''\n|-\n| [[Tyrone Guthrie]]\n| ''[[The Tenth Man (Chayefsky play)|The Tenth Man]]''\n|-\n| [[Elia Kazan]]\n| ''[[Sweet Bird of Youth]]''\n|-\n| [[Lloyd Richards]]\n| ''[[A Raisin in the Sun]]''\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" align=\"center\"| '''1961'''<br>{{small|[[15th Tony Awards]]}}\n|- style=\"background:#B0C4DE\"\n| [[John Gielgud]]\n| ''[[Big Fish, Little Fish (play)|Big Fish, Little Fish]]''\n|-\n| [[Joseph Anthony]]\n| ''[[Rhinoceros (play)|Rhinoceros]]''\n|-\n| [[Joan Littlewood]]\n| ''[[The Hostage (play)|The Hostage]]''\n|-\n| [[Arthur Penn]]\n| ''[[All the Way Home (play)|All the Way Home]]''\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" align=\"center\"| '''1962'''<br>{{small|[[16th Tony Awards]]}}\n|- style=\"background:#B0C4DE\"\n| [[Noel Willman]]\n| ''[[A Man for All Seasons]]''\n|-\n| [[Tyrone Guthrie]]\n| ''[[Gideon (play)|Gideon]]''\n|-\n| [[Donald McWhinnie]]\n| ''[[The Caretaker]]''\n|-\n| [[Jos\u00e9 Quintero]]\n| ''Great Day in the Morning''\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" align=\"center\"| '''1963'''<br>{{small|[[17th Tony Awards]]}}\n|- style=\"background:#B0C4DE\"\n| [[Alan Schneider]]\n| ''[[Who's Afraid of Virginia Woolf?]]''\n|-\n| [[George Abbott]]\n| ''[[Never Too Late (play)|Never Too Late]]''\n|-\n| [[John Gielgud]]\n| ''[[The School for Scandal]]''\n|-\n| [[Peter Glenville]]\n| ''[[Tchin-Tchin]]''\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" align=\"center\"| '''1964'''<br>{{small|[[18th Tony Awards]]}}\n|- style=\"background:#B0C4DE\"\n| [[Mike Nichols]]\n| ''[[Barefoot in the Park]]''\n|-\n| [[June Havoc]]\n| ''Marathon '33''\n|-\n| [[Alan Schneider]]\n| ''[[The Ballad of the Sad Caf\u00e9]]''\n|-\n| [[Herman Shumlin]]\n| ''[[The Deputy]]''\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\" align=\"center\"| '''1965'''<br>{{small|[[19th Tony Awards]]}}\n|- style=\"background:#B0C4DE\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[Mike Nichols]]\n| ''[[Luv (play)|Luv]]''\n|- style=\"background:#B0C4DE\"\n| ''[[The Odd Couple (play)|The Odd Couple]]''\n|-\n| [[William Ball (director)|William Ball]]\n| ''[[Tartuffe]]''\n|-\n| [[Ulu Grosbard]]\n| ''[[The Subject Was Roses]]''\n|-\n| [[Alan Schneider]]\n| ''[[Tiny Alice]]''\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" align=\"center\"| '''1966'''<br>{{small|[[20th Tony Awards]]}}\n|- style=\"background:#B0C4DE\"\n| [[Peter Brook]]\n| ''[[Marat/Sade]]''\n|-\n| [[Hilton Edwards]]\n| ''[[Philadelphia, Here I Come!]]''\n|-\n| [[Ellis Rabb]]\n| ''[[You Can't Take It with You (play)|You Can't Take It with You]]''\n|-\n| [[Noel Willman]]\n| ''[[The Lion in Winter]]''\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" align=\"center\"| '''1967'''<br>{{small|[[21st Tony Awards]]}}\n|- style=\"background:#B0C4DE\"\n| [[Peter Hall (director)|Peter Hall]]\n| ''[[The Homecoming]]''