ed September 27, 2017</ref>\n* Mary Zimmerman \u2013 ''[[Metamorphoses (play)|Metamorphoses]]'' (2002)<ref>[http://www.playbill.com/article/2002-tony-award-direction-of-a-play-mary-zimmerman-metamorphoses-com-106197 \"2002 Tony Award Direction of a Play\"] Playbill, retrieved September 27, 2017</ref>\n* Anna D. Shapiro \u2013 ''[[August: Osage County]]'' (2008)<ref>[http://www.playbill.com/article/just-the-facts-list-of-2008-tony-award-winners-and-nominees-com-150935 \"Just the Facts: List of 2008 Tony Award Winners and Nominees\"] Playbill, retrieved September 27, 2017</ref>\n* Pam MacKinnon \u2013 ''[[Who's Afraid of Virginia Woolf?]]'' revival (2013)<ref>[https://www.cbsnews.com/news/tony-awards-2013-list-of-winners/ \"Tony Awards 2013 List of Winners\"] CBS News, retrieved September 27, 2017</ref>\n* Marianne Elliott \u2013 ''[[War Horse (play)|War Horse]]'' (2011) (shared with Tom Morris)<ref>[https://variety.com/2011/legit/news/2011-tony-award-winners-list-1118038436/] Variety, retrieved September 27, 2017</ref> and ''[[The Curious Incident of the Dog in the Night-Time (play)|The Curious Incident of the Dog in the Night-Time]]'' (2015)<ref>[http://www.playbill.com/article/2015-tony-awards-just-the-winners-please-com-350800 \"2015 Tony Awards Just the Winners Please\"] Playbill, retrieved September 27, 2017</ref>, making her the only woman to win this award more than once\n* Rebecca Taichman \u2013 ''[[Indecent (play)|Indecent]]'' (2017)<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2017/06/11/theater/tony-winners-list.html?mcubz=1\"Tony Winners List\"] ''The New York Times'', retrieved September 27, 2017</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Tony Award for Best Direction of a Musical]]\n* [[Drama Desk Award for Outstanding Director of a Play]]\n* [[Laurence Olivier Award for Best Director]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.ibdb.com/advSearchAwards.php Tony Award for Direction of a Play ibdb]\n* [http://www.tonyawards.com/p/tonys_search Tony Awards official site]\n\n{{TonyAward PlayDirection}}\n{{TonyAwardsbyYear}}\n\n[[Category:Tony Awards]]\n[[Category:Awards established in 1960]]\n[[Category:1960 establishments in the United States]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox award\n| name        = [[Tony Award]] for <br>Best Direction of a Play\n| description = Best Direction of a Play\n| presenter   = [[American Theatre Wing]] [[The Broadway League]]\n| location    = [[New York City]]\n| holder      = [[Sam Mendes]] for ''[[The Ferryman (play)|The Ferryman]]'' {{small|(2019)}}\n| website     = [http://www.tonyawards.com/en_US/index.html TonyAwards.com]\n}}\nThe '''[[Tony Award]] for Best Direction of a Play''' has been given since 1960.  Before 1960 there was only one award for both play direction and musical direction, then in 1960 the award was split into two categories: ''Dramatic'' and ''Musical''.  In 1976 the Dramatic category was renamed to Play.  For pre-1960 direction awards please reference [[Tony Award for Best Director]].\n\n==Winners and nominees==\n{{legend|#B0C4DE|indicates the winner}}\n\n===1960s===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:98%;\"\n|- style=\"background:#bebebe;\"\n! style=\"width:11%;\"| Year\n! style=\"width:35%;\"| Director\n! style=\"width:54%;\"| Production\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\" align=\"center\"| '''1960'''<br>{{small|[[14th Tony Awards]]}}\n|- style=\"background:#B0C4DE\"\n| [[Arthur Penn]]\n| ''[[The Miracle Worker (play)|The Miracle Worker]]''\n|-\n| [[Joseph Anthony]]\n| ''[[The Best Man (play)|The Best Man]]''\n|-\n| [[Tyrone Guthrie]]\n| ''[[The Tenth Man (Chayefsky play)|The Tenth Man]]''\n|-\n| [[Elia Kazan]]\n| ''[[Sweet Bird of Youth]]''\n|-\n| [[Lloyd Richards]]\n| ''[[A Raisin in the Sun]]''\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" align=\"center\"| '''1961'''<br>{{small|[[15th Tony Awards]]}}\n|- style=\"background:#B0C4DE\"\n| [[John Gielgud]]\n| ''[[Big Fish, Little Fish (play)|Big Fish, Little Fish]]''\n|-\n| [[Joseph Anthony]]\n| ''[[Rhinoceros (play)|Rhinoceros]]''\n|-\n| [[Joan Littlewood]]\n|